1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Welcome to the first session of migrating your website.

2
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:08,280
In this lesson we will explore how you can change hosting providers as well as your domain

3
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:12,920
name.

4
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:14,840
Why would someone want to migrate their site?

5
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:17,920
Well, some of the reasons might be due to moving to a new host, changing your domain name

6
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:23,120
or moving from HTTP to HTTPS.

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
This tutorial is right for you if you want to move WordPress hosts as well as change

8
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:31,320
your domain name.

9
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:33,920
All you will need to do is set up a new site and install a migration plugin on both your

10
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:38,400
old and new websites.

11
00:00:37,720 --> 00:00:40,720
And also remember to make a backup of your site on a device before starting the migration.

12
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:47,160
There are various migration plugins available in the Plugins Directory.

13
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:52,440
Plugins such as Duplicator, Backup Migration and All-in-One WordPress Migration are just

14
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:57,640
some of the plugins worth exploring.

15
00:00:57,560 --> 00:01:00,560
Some hosts even have their own migration plugins if you were planning to move your site to

16
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:05,040
them.

17
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:06,040
Today I am going to use the All-in-One WordPress migration plugin.

18
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:11,480
So once you have set up your new domain with your new host, let's make our way to the front

19
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:16,800
end of our old website which we are of course going to transfer to a new home.

20
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,120
Our first tip now is to make our way to the dashboard, head to plugins and add the All-

21
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:37,920
in-One migration plugin.

22
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:42,880
Once it is installed and activated, we will make our way to the plugin in the left sidebar

23
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:54,120
and then click on Export to and then select File.

24
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
It is also advised to export to an external drive to ensure you have a backup.

25
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:07,680
When you click on File, it will start preparing the export.

26
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:13,320
And once completed, we can click on Download and download the file to our computer.

27
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:23,360
The next step is to make our way to our new domain and install the plugin there as well.

28
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:30,400
We need the plugin on the old website and the new one as we are exporting and importing

29
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:35,560
from one to the other.

30
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:38,640
And once the plugin has been installed and activated, we can hover over the plugin in

31
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:43,760
the left sidebar and click on Import.

32
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:48,240
And now we are going to import or upload the file from our computer.

33
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:59,400
And please take note, this might take a few minutes.

34
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:04,560
And once the process has been completed, we can click on Proceed as we have not added

35
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:09,400
any other content to the new site.

36
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:13,400
And lastly, Finish.

37
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:15,880
And now if we make our way to the front end of our new domain, we will see that the entire

38
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:21,280
site has been transferred or migrated.

39
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:30,400
Before we end off, there is one last consideration.

40
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:33,280
If you were concerned about SEO, it is advised to set up 301 redirects.

41
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:39,760
A 301 redirect indicates to search engines that a page has been moved permanently.

42
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:45,800
It basically means that if users request an old URL, they will automatically be sent

43
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,600
to a new URL.

44
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:53,280
There are a few ways to do this, but the easiest way is to use a plugin such as Redirection,

45
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:59,120
Simple 301 Redirects or All-in-One SEO

46
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:02,680
to ensure you don't lose your website's search engine rankings, traffic and conversions.

47
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:08,920
You can search the Plugins Directory to find the right plugin for you.

48
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:13,560
But I did want to mention some plugins may offer additional and faster ways to set up

49
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:18,360
redirects through paid features.

50
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:20,840
But it is also possible to change the redirects one by one using many free versions of plugins.

51
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:28,160
All the best migrating your site to a new hosting provider and domain name.

